<subSubSection id="6894D3871A1BFFA5FF6F80C4FC349C34" lastPageId="27" lastPageNumber="178" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="2031800C1A1BFFA5FF6F80C4FC349C34" blockId="26.[151,1437,942,2013]" lastBlockId="27.[151,1437,151,285]" lastPageId="27" lastPageNumber="178" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">
<emphasis id="12FA5C1E1A1BFFA4FF6F80C4FE929AF4" bold="true" box="[199,315,1987,2013]" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">Remarks.</emphasis>
The male from 
<collectingRegion id="E24A4EEE1A1BFFA4FE4580C4FD8C9AF4" box="[493,549,1987,2013]" country="Russia" name="Altay" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">Altai</collectingRegion>
matches 
<taxonomicName id="E78EFB8F1A1BFFA4FD2680C4FC8E9AF4" authorityName="Bidzilya &amp; Karsholt" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Junnilainen" baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[654,807,1987,2013]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Ptycerata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perexigella">
<emphasis id="12FA5C1E1A1BFFA4FD2680C4FC8E9AF4" box="[654,807,1987,2013]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">P. perexigella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from S. Ural both externally and in the genitalia, except for its slightly larger size (wingspan 
<quantity id="E7762DE91A1AFFA5FDE18790FD369D98" box="[585,671,151,177]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" unit="mm" value="11.0">11 mm</quantity>
), and shorter and broader saccus. A male from Namangan differs externally in having the forewings lighter, pale and mottled with brown-tipped scales, and in larger wingspan (
<quantity id="E7762DE91A1AFFA5FA2887BCFF6E9DD0" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" unit="mm" value="12.0">12 mm</quantity>
). The genitalia of this specimen are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="E78EFB8F1A1AFFA5FC9787D8FC709DD0" authorityName="Bidzilya &amp; Karsholt" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Junnilainen" baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[831,985,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Ptycerata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perexigella">
<emphasis id="12FA5C1E1A1AFFA5FC9787D8FC709DD0" box="[831,985,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">P. perexigella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in general. However, the differences in shape of uncus, gnathos, valva and saccus suggest a separate species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
